omposite of profitability, return on capital, balance-sheet safety and cash conversion (the Fundamentals-tab Quality score).","why_useful":"A durable, high-return business compounds value; a low-quality one needs a bigger margin of safety.","why_it_can_fail":"A single composite can mask a weak component; open the Fundamentals tab for the breakdown."},{"label":"Cash conversion","value":0.67,"unit":"\u00d7","status":"ok","read":"0.67\u00d7 \u2014 partly cash-backed.","meaning":"Median of (cash from operations \u00f7 net profit) over the last 5 years.","why_useful":"Profit you can't collect as cash is fragile; >0.8\u00d7 means earnings are real cash, <0.6\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.1,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"good","read":"Conservatively financed (D/E 0.10\u00d7, interest cover 4.7\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":-73.41,"unit":"% YoY","status":"weak","read":"Profit down 73% YoY (latest TTM).","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":315.7,"pe_percentile":100.0,"median_pe":30.8,"earnings_yield_pct":0.32,"pb":14.26,"ev_ebitda":101.13,"quality_score":78.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":0.0